primaryTopic.definition: In July 1994 the Materials Research Laboratory and Aeronautical Research Laboratory merged to form the Aeronautical and Maritime Research Laboratory (AMRL). A restructure of the Defence Science and Technology Organisation in 2002 resulted in the closure of all existing research Laboratories for the creation of three new ones. (Courtesy of Encyclopedia of Australian Science)
